title: Grateful Dead Live at Radio City Music Hall on 1980-10-23
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1/Dolby B) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> Samplitude Professional v10.21 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

On The Road Again, It Must Have Been The Roses, Dark Hollow, Jack A Roe, Cassidy, China Doll, Monkey & The Engineer, Ain't No Lie-> Ripple

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Tennessee Jed, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, Little Red Rooster, Big Railroad Blues, The Music Never Stopped

Set 3

Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Casey Jones

First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text: Dial it Up! Just to hear the crowd swell when Jerry starts singing China Doll is worth the price of admission...

Concerts are for dancing. It is hard to listen to the first set of this show because somebody is yelling "down in front" the whole time and "sit down". 33 years later and the dude is still a buzzkill. I hate "sit-down" shows.
Fun among the audience  Very nice show, and this recording has lots of energy.
